==English==
===Adjective===
# Possessing [[money]].
#: 1933: ''We're In The Money'' &mdash; song title, lyrics [[w:Al Dubin|Al Dubin]], music [[w:Harry Warren|Harry Warren]] [http://www.harrywarren.org/songs/0140.htm]
# {{finance}} For an [[option]], having a [[strike]] price which makes it profitable to exercise.  For a [[call]] this is a strike below the market price, or for a [[put]] a strike above the market price.
#: ''the deep-in-the-money call position (April 40 calls) does not offer anywhere near the profit potential nor leverage of the other trades'' &mdash;  Jay Kaeppel, Optionetics [http://www.optionetics.com/articles/article_full.asp?idNo=13861]
